<Author>gocougsBellingham
<Content>Great pre-flight hotel Stayed at Hilton Garden Inn the night before our return flight home. I am a very picky traveler especially regarding hotels and I found this property to be very nice for this category hotel. Front desk staff were very friendly and helpful. Beds were some of the most comfortable we have experienced at any hotel, including higher end hotels. Our best night of sleep on our 11 day trip. Great pool for this size hotel. Breakfast in the morning was very good, with excellent service. We had breakfast included in our rate of $137 per night for 2 adults, 2 children.Hotel is a little further away from the airport than other hotels such as the Embassy Suites, but only by about 5-10 mins.Not many restaurants in the immediate area other than fast food. As there is freeway access right outside the entrance to the hotel, we chose an italian restaurant Buca Di Beppo for dinner. It is about 15 min. North on the freeway. Dinner was quite good with large portions and is in a very nice area. Hotel can give you directions.When we come back for our next cruise, would definitely stay here again! 
